SUMMARY:BIG In-Person/Online Meetup (East Columbia Branch Library) [Postmortem: Desktop Golf]
DESCRIPTION:In-person is at the East Columbia Branch Library in the Marvin Thomas Room. \nJoin us IN-PERSON or ONLINE. Anyone with an interest in game design and development is welcome\, from beginners to veteran professionals. \nWe will be meeting in the Marvin Thomas Room at the East Columbia Branch Library (6600 Cradlerock Way). (Not an official Howard County Library System event.) \nThe developer of Desktop Golf will give a postmortem talk on the game. \nIf you want to attend virtually\, the Discord server link is provided in the main monthly (1st of the month) meetup details. An organizer will ensure that a laptop is provided on-site to connect the Discord attendees with those physically on-site. It takes us a few minutes to set up the projector\, so hold tight when you join the Discord voice chat channel. We’ll be there soon!
URL:https://baltimoreindiegames.com/event/in-person-online-meetup-east-columbia-branch-library/
LOCATION:East Columbia Branch
END:VEVENT
