SUMMARY:Awesome Con
DESCRIPTION:The Indie Showcase is taking over an entire salon at Awesome Con and we want YOU to be there! \nWe have TONS of space this year and welcome any game in any form be it a traditional PC\, alt.ctrl\, homebrew\, console\, etc. As long as it’s in a playable state\, we want to show it off! \nYour showcase space is free and you’ll be given 3 badges\, a 6ft table\, 4 chairs\, and access to a power drop to work with. \nAwesome Con is the perfect place to get feedback on a new prototype or fine tune your main project before launch. The convention reaches a broad audience\, especially in the family and youth demographic. Awesome Con is also a great “training wheels” event if you’ve never shown a game in a convention setting before. Did we mention it’s free to show? \nThe submission deadline to Sunday\, January 18th. Click the button below to apply and please share the link out to any fellow developers who may be interested! If you know of a school program\, STEAM\, or game dev club that would also be interested in showing off\, have them email la****@*****st.org. \nhttps://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSc47Vfltb7LTLezZbZPj-S8ReP7Ry62L-9jFlJS1sXvrHvm9Q/viewform
URL:https://baltimoreindiegames.com/event/awesome-con/
LOCATION:Walter E. Washington Convention Center\, 801 Mt Vernon Pl NW\, Washington\, DC\, 20001\, United States
END:VEVENT
