SUMMARY:MoComCon 2026
DESCRIPTION:Montgomery County Public Libraries is celebrating 10-years of MoComCon this March! \nMoComCon is a FREE celebration of all things comics\, graphic novels\, and fandoms! \nAs part of this year’s programming\, MoComCon is hosting a Gaming Industry Panel to give attendees an inside look at the world of video game creation and development.\n\nPanel Details:\n\nTopic: The Gaming Industry – Insights from Creators\n\nFormat: 45-minute panel (10-15-minute presentation per group\, followed by Q&A)\n\nAudience: Gamers\, aspiring developers\, and pop culture enthusiasts\n\n  \nFriday\, March 20\, 2026\nBlackRock Center for the Arts\n6:00 PM – 8: 00 PM\nEvening event for Teens & Adults \nSaturday\, March 21\, 2026\nGermantown Library\n10:00 AM – 4:00 PM\nKid & Family friendly events \nSaturday\, March 21\, 2026\nBlackRock Center for the Arts\n11:00 AM – 5:00 PM\nEvents for Teens & Adults
URL:https://baltimoreindiegames.com/event/mocomcon-2026/
LOCATION:Black Rock Center for the Arts\, 12901 Town Commons Dr\, Germantown\, MD\, 20874\, United States
END:VEVENT
